<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-75-1014 </DOCNO><TEXT>Natural gas has a market share of circa 17% in the Western European energysupply. Some people claim it could be 30%. It is explained that thisclaim is too ambitious, because marketing of natural gas is essentiallydifferent from marketing oil, coal or other important sources. Also theinfluence of Europe 1992, the European integration, on the gas marketis discussed. Special attention is paid to the idea of a common carrier:a public gas transport system. 4 figs.</TEXT></DOC>